  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nGossipsub stores all received messages into the memcache and gossips about all historic messages. We don't want to advertise invalid messages and these should be removed from the memcache. \r\n\r\nThere are a few solutions to this: \r\n1. Prevent gossip for invalidated messages (this will still store invalidated messages in the LRU Time cache bloating RAM).\r\n2. Add callbacks to invalidate messages which removes them from the memcache. \r\n3. Add a timeout to messages which removes messages that have not been validated in a given time frame. \r\n\r\nIt's likely that we will go with a combination of 1 and 2. ",
